# Component Patterns

Every component is a piece of glass. Consistency matters — use these patterns exactly.

## Buttons

### Primary (solid brand color)
```css
.btn-primary {
  background: var(--color-sky);
  color: var(--color-gray-900);
  font: var(--text-headline);
  border: none;
  border-radius: 999px;
  padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-24);
  min-height: 50px;
  width: 100%;
  transition: transform 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1),
              opacity 0.2s ease;
}
.btn-primary:active { transform: scale(0.97); opacity: 0.85; }
```

### Secondary (glass)
```css
.btn-secondary {
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
  backdrop-filter: blur(20px) saturate(150%);
  color: var(--color-sky);
  font: var(--text-headline);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
  border-radius: 999px;
  padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-24);
  min-height: 50px;
}
```

### Small / Pill
- Same glass or solid style, but `padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-16)` and `min-height: 36px`.

## Inputs

```css
.input {
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
  backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
  border-radius: 16px;
  padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-16);
  font: var(--text-body);
  color: var(--color-gray-900);
  min-height: 48px;
}
.input:focus {
  border-color: var(--color-sky);
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(90,200,250,0.25);
  outline: none;
}
```

## Cards

Glass cards are the primary content container.

```css
.card {
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
  backdrop-filter: blur(40px) saturate(180%);
  border-radius: 24px;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
  box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  padding: var(--space-20);
}
```

## Bottom Tab Bar (Floating Glass)

```css
.tab-bar {
  position: fixed;
  bottom: calc(var(--space-12) + var(--safe-bottom));
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--space-4);
  padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-8);
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
  backdrop-filter: blur(40px) saturate(180%);
  border-radius: 999px;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
  box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}
.tab-bar-item {
  min-width: 44px;
  min-height: 44px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  border-radius: 999px;
}
.tab-bar-item.active {
  background: rgba(90,200,250,0.2);
}
```

## Modals / Sheets

- Slide up from the bottom (iOS-style sheet).
- Use `border-radius: 24px 24px 0 0` on the sheet.
- Full glass treatment on the sheet surface.
- Dimmed backdrop: `background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3)` with `backdrop-filter: blur(8px)`.
- Include a drag handle: `40px` wide, `4px` tall, centered, `border-radius: 999px`, `background: rgba(0,0,0,0.15)`.

## Rules

1. **All interactive elements are at least 44x44px.** No exceptions.
2. **Full-width buttons** for primary actions. Pill buttons for secondary/inline.
3. **No outlines or borders for visual-only decoration** — borders exist only on glass edges for the light-catch effect.
4. **Icons inside buttons** sit left of text with `--space-8` gap.
